UoC will contribute the Stilwell video production. Scripts for the five to six video clips will be co-produced with
participants and represent yr2, final year 5, F1, F2 and then 5+ experienced. A film production team
including professional actors will produce the video series.

A professionally directed, acted and produced series of a virtual medical community or medical 'soap
opera': with audio-video clips of doctor-patient, doctor-staff, doctor-next of kin interactions; which
focus on and illustrate the development of phronesis through the practical resolution of ethical
dilemmas. This would become a resource for Medical Schools, Health Education England, NHS (both
primary and secondary care) and other medical and allied healthcare educational establishments.</gtr:partnerContribution><gtr:piContribution>Mervyn Conroy (PI) is a Senior Fellow at HSMC will lead all activities including collaborations to ensure that the project's aims and
